                                                   Bangla on backfoot
                      
	Chittagong: South Africa paceman Dale Steyn took three wickets for four runs to reduce Bangladesh in their second innings, to 54 for five at close of play on the third day of the second Test on Sunday.         
	Bangladesh were dismissed for 259 and were asked to follow on just after tea.         
